    HASKELL DEPS

# basic deps
transformers mtl deepseq data-ordlist cereal text stm network

attoparsec # Derive: tracklang parsing
fixed-list-0.1.5 # Derive.Call.Util: for typesafe mapping
mersenne-random-pure64 hashable random-shuffle # Derive: score randomization
storablevector # control signals (drags in: QuickCheck utility-ht non-negative)
vector # pitch signals
dlist # Perform.SignalBase

hint # lang repl
haskeline # repl

parsec # Instrument.Parse, could use attoparsec, but parsec errors are better
haskell-src # Util.PPrint
regex-pcre # Util.Test

utf8-string # Ui.Event

shake # build system

    INSTALLED SEPARATELY

libpcre library from http://www.pcre.org

lilypond, for some fonts

    OS X:
    cp LilyPond.app/Contents/Resources/share/lilypond/current/fonts/otf/emmentaler* ~/Library/Fonts

    Linux:
    cp /usr/share/lilypond/<version>/fonts/otf/ ~/.fonts
    # or
    cp /usr/share/lilypond/<version>/fonts/otf/ /usr/share/fonts/

    non haskell deps

fltk-1.3

libpcre, for regex-pcre.  OS X port puts headers in /opt where configure may
not find them.

    MISC

tools/run_profile expects ps2pdf in the path, which is part of ghostscript.
